'''Rakuten Viki'''是一家美國[[影音|影音]][[串流媒體|串流媒體]]網站，總部位於[[加州|加州]][[聖馬刁_(加利福尼亞州)|聖馬刁]]<ref name="WSJ">{{Cite journal|title=Singapore Start-up Sees Gold Mine In Foreign Language TV|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/searealtime/2011/10/21/singapore-start-up-sees-gold-mine-in-foreign-language-tv/|last=Holmes|first=Sam|journal=[[华尔街日报|华尔街日报]]|accessdate=January 25, 2013|year=2011|archive-date=2012-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121031121712/http://blogs.wsj.com/searealtime/2011/10/21/singapore-start-up-sees-gold-mine-in-foreign-language-tv/}}</ref>。该公司还在[[新加坡|新加坡]]、[[東京|東京]]和[[首爾|首爾]]设有办事处<ref>{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DvTh7E_ck4Q|title=Viki Office Tour - Coolest Places in Singapore: Episode 1 (January 28)|publisher=|accessdate=December 3, 2015|archive-date=2015-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151118014113/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DvTh7E_ck4Q}}</ref>。 

Viki這個名字是video（影片）和[[Wiki|Wiki]]的合成詞。Viki在2011年1月獲得了[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]最佳國際初創公司獎<ref name="TC4">{{Cite journal|title=Congratulations Crunchies Winners! Twitter Takes Best Startup of 2010|url=https://techcrunch.com/2011/01/21/congratulations-crunchies-winners-twitter-takes-best-startup-of-2010/|last=Rao|first=Leena|journal=TechCrunch|accessdate=January 25, 2013|year=2011|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204075727/https://techcrunch.com/2011/01/21/congratulations-crunchies-winners-twitter-takes-best-startup-of-2010/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 歷史 ==

2007年，{{link-en|Razmig Hovaghimian}}、Changseong Ho和Jiwon Moon創辦了Viki。公司的資金最初來源於Neoteny Labs（一個由Joichi Ito領導的[[新加坡|新加坡]][[初创企业|初创企业]]基金），以及[[領英|領英]]的聯合創始人[[Reid_Hoffman|Reid Hoffman]]<ref name="WSJ2">{{cite journal|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390443921504577643773810338032|title=Breaking Down Language Barriers - WSJ|author=Holmes, Sam|year=2012|journal=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]]|access-date=December 3, 2015|archive-date=2021-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210507180709/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390443921504577643773810338032}}</ref>。2008年，公司搬遷至新加坡，以利用當地政府的慷慨支持，以及這個[[城邦|城市國家]]泛亞洲樞紐的地位<ref name=TC1>{{cite journal | last=Lacy | first=Sarah | year=2010 | title=ViKi Raises $4.3 Million from VC All-Stars to Translate the World's Video | url=https://techcrunch.com/2010/12/08/viki-raises-4-3-million-from-vc-all-stars-to-translate-the-worlds-video/?icid=tc_marc-andreessen_art&tag=marc-andreessen | journal=TechCrunch | access-date=January 25, 2013 | archive-date=2021-05-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210510142357/https://techcrunch.com/2010/12/08/viki-raises-4-3-million-from-vc-all-stars-to-translate-the-worlds-video/?icid=tc_marc-andreessen_art&tag=marc-andreessen }}</ref>。2010年12月，Viki結束了[[軟件版本週期#Beta|Beta測試]]並且向大衆公開了他們的服務<ref name=AN>{{cite journal| last=Bertschy| first=Zac| year=2012| title=Interview: Razmig Hovaghimian, Cofounder and CEO of Viki.com| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interview/2012-04-25/interview-razmig-hovaghimian-co-founder-and-ceo-of-viki.com| journal=[[Anime_News_Network|Anime News Network]]| access-date=January 25, 2013| archive-date=2021-01-26| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126053454/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interview/2012-04-25/interview-razmig-hovaghimian-co-founder-and-ceo-of-viki.com}}</ref>。2013年9月，該公司被日本[[樂天_(Rakuten)|樂天株式會社 (Rakuten)]]以2億美元收購<ref name=allthingsd0913>{{cite journal | author = Swisher, Kara | year = 2013 | url = http://allthingsd.com/20130901/exclusive-japans-rakuten-acquires-viki-video-site-for-200-million | title = Exclusive: Japan's Rakuten Acquires Viki Video Site for $200 Million | journal = ， AllThingsD | access-date = December 3, 2015 | archive-date = 2015-12-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151209212048/http://allthingsd.com/20130901/exclusive-japans-rakuten-acquires-viki-video-site-for-200-million/ }}</ref>。

== 服務 ==
Viki提供優質且授權的視頻串流服務，與[[Hulu|Hulu]]在[[美國|美國]]提供的服務類似<ref name=WSJ/>。該網站會把視頻放在不同的頻道中。視頻可以由社區志願者添加字幕<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.viki.com/community_resources|title=Rakuten Viki|website=www.viki.com|access-date=June 1, 2019|archive-date=2019-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710133302/https://www.viki.com/community_resources}}</ref>。Viki是第一個支持在所有視頻類型中實時添加字幕和协作的平台。社區志願者可以使用Viki的字幕技術，爲他們喜歡的視頻添加多種語言的字幕，这爲全球協作提供了便利。添加的字幕以[[知识共享许可协议|知识共享许可协议]]授權<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.viki.com/terms_of_use#toc-submissions|title=Rakuten Viki Terms of Use Section 8.3.2|website=www.viki.com|access-date=June 1, 2019|archive-date=2019-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221183232/https://www.viki.com/terms_of_use#toc-submissions}}</ref>。該公司開發的字幕軟體支持翻譯200多種語言<ref name=WSJ/>。Viki也會將志願者添加的字幕發放給諸如Hulu、[[Netflix|Netflix]]和[[雅虎|雅虎]]之類的合作夥伴，從這些電影分銷商中收取費用、賺得收入。這200多種語言中，有大約50種屬於[[瀕危語言|脆弱或瀕危語言]]。<ref>{{cite journal | author=Park, Madison | year=2014 | url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/06/09/world/asia/international-dramas-viki/index.html?hpt=hp_c4 | title=Can Fans Unravel the Babel of the World's Dramas? | journal=CNN | access-date=December 3, 2015 | archive-date=2017-08-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820034840/http://edition.cnn.com/2014/06/09/world/asia/international-dramas-viki/index.html?hpt=hp_c4 }}</ref>

